Step Functions: lm(), I()

(r = lm(ozone ~ I(temperature >= 40) + I(temperature >= 55) + I(temperature >= 70) + I(temperature >= 85), data=ozone))

Call:

    55) + I(temperature >= 70) + I(temperature >= 85), data = ozone)

# with many cut points
(form = paste0("ozone ~ ",paste0("I(temperature >= ", seq(35,85,by=5), ")", collapse=" + ")))

with(ozone, plot(temperature, ozone))
lines(newx$temperature, yhat, col="red")       # add a curve

Smoothing Splines: smooth.spline()

with(ozone, plot(temperature, ozone))
df = 2:6                                      # degrees of freedom 
for(j in df) {
  r = smooth.spline(ozone$ozone ~ ozone$temperature, df = j)
  yhat = predict(r, newx)$y[[1]]
  lines(newx$temperature, yhat, lty=j, col=j)  
}
legend(25, 35, leg=paste0("df = ", df), lty=df, col=df)

Local Regression: loess()

with(ozone, plot(temperature, ozone))
span = 2:5/10                                      # span
for(j in span) {
  r = loess(ozone ~ temperature, data=ozone, span = j)
  yhat = predict(r, newx)                          # prediction
  lines(newx$temperature, yhat, lty=j*10, col=j*10)        # add a curve
}
legend(25, 35, leg=paste0("span = ", span), lty=span*10, col=span*10)
